gresolver
------------------------------------------
GResolver is a graphical DNS query tool. It allows system administrators
to quickly and easily make the most common DNS queries without
constructing lengthy dig commands.

GResolver supports all the main resource record types, including AAAA,
AXFR, MX and TXT, and the appropriate in-addr.arpa address is
constructed from dotted-quad IP addresses when doing PTR queries. There
are checkboxes for controlling the most commonly-used options.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.21-1
  bind-9.3.2-1
  perl-5.8.7-5
  perl-Gtk2-1.122-1
  perl-Gtk2-GladeXML-1.005-1
  perl-Locale-gettext-1.05-1
  perl-Net-IPv6Addr-0.2-1

Build requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.21-1
  cygport-0.2.5-1
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-1

Canonical website:
  http://jodrell.net/projects/gresolver

Canonical download:
  http://jodrell.net/files/gresolver/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack gresolver-0.0.5-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./gresolver-0.0.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gresolver-0.0.5-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/gresolver-0.0.5-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

  /usr/bin/gresolver
  /usr/share/applications/gresolver.desktop
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/gresolver-0.0.5.README
  /usr/share/doc/gresolver-0.0.5/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/gresolver-0.0.5/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/gresolver/gresolver.glade
  /usr/share/pixmaps/gresolver.png

